A man believed to be in his 30s fell to his death during a paragliding accident in Centurion, Pretoria on Sunday afternoon, paramedics said. Shortly before 5pm, paramedics from ER24 arrived on the scene where they found a bystander performing cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) on the man, ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. Paramedics assessed him and found that there is unfortunately nothing further that they could do for him and he was declared dead on the scene. The exact circumstances surrounding the incident are not known to paramedics and will be investigated, he said. African News Agency (ANA) ALSO READ: Biker dies in N12 Benoni crash For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.